pg?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/Esker_Smokey_Steel_02.jpg?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/Esker_Smokey_Steel_02.jpg?resize=2048,2048&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>4130 Shred Sled</strong></p>\n<p>Esker builds its steel hardtails from 4130 Chromoly double-butted, seamless tubes provide a greater strength-to-weight ratio than for the utmost durability and ride quality. The brand uses a complete Electrophoretic Deposition (ED) coating of the frame resists corrosion inside and out for an extremely long and worry-free life.</p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/pages/smokey\" target=\"_blank\">Esker Cycles</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/esker-cycles-steel-smokey-160-mm-hardtail/\">Esker Cycles Steel Smokey 160 mm Hardtail</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"71463829766286ca35206de854ef182155af570142d9d8b9c76b6a8ac5c6534c","category":"Cycling"}